<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,570,881]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,762,786]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is tentatively included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1917" box="[721,817,762,785]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,817,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Maiestas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pending the examination of males. It can be distinguished externally by the extra cross veins in the forewing and a fine brown line parallel to the fore margin of the head either side of the midline. The former character would key out the species in the first couplet of Dash &amp; Viraktamath’s, 1998 key.
</paragraph>
